Jane Street is hosting an Estimathon™ at UC Berkeley on Tuesday, March 1 @ 6pm in the Woz! An Estimathon™ is a favorite game amongst Streeters that brings together math and trivia. 

Register here by Feb 27th @ 11:59pm. 

We hope to see you there!
-Jane Street Recruiting

Jane Street Estimathon™ at UC Berkeley!
Tuesday, March 1 @ 6:00pm PT 

The Estimathon™ is a mind-bending mixture of math and trivia. In teams, you'll attempt 13 Fermi problems in 30 minutes, ranging from totally trivial to positively Putnamesque. Be prepared to come up with the best set of confidence intervals! Sample problems include:
How many stop signs are in New York City?
How many babies were born in 1900?
How many Social Security Numbers are prime?

Register here by Feb 27 @ 11:59pm PT. All participants will register as an individual and teams will be created on-site. We will confirm your attendance and event location by Feb 28. 

COVID Policies: All participants must be fully vaccinated in order to attend. For the purposes of this event, fully vaccinated means 6 weeks after the single dose J&J, 3 weeks after the second dose of Pfizer, and 2 weeks after the second dose of Moderna. This event will be indoors, so masks will be required.
history.subject: Jane Street Estimathon! RSVP by 2/27
